{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"Our grandparents' generation\ncreated an amazing system"},{"time":4600,"text":"of canals and reservoirs\nthat made it possible"},{"time":7200,"text":"for people to live in places\nwhere there wasn't a lot of water."},{"time":10640,"text":"For example, during the Great Depression,"},{"time":13200,"text":"they created the Hoover Dam,"},{"time":14840,"text":"which in turn, created Lake Mead"},{"time":17280,"text":"and made it possible for the cities\nof Las Vegas and Phoenix"},{"time":20920,"text":"and Los Angeles to provide water"},{"time":22680,"text":"for people who lived\nin a really dry place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25760,"text":"In the 20th century,\nwe literally spent trillions of dollars"},{"time":29680,"text":"building infrastructure\nto get water to our cities."},{"time":33120,"text":"In terms of economic development,\nit was a great investment."},{"time":37080,"text":"But in the last decade,\nwe've seen the combined effects"},{"time":40080,"text":"of climate change, population growth\nand competition for water resources"},{"time":45880,"text":"threaten these vital lifelines\nand water resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49560,"text":"This figure shows you the change\nin the lake level of Lake Mead"},{"time":53720,"text":"that happened in the last 15 years."},{"time":56000,"text":"You can see starting around the year 2000,"},{"time":58360,"text":"the lake level started to drop."},{"time":60280,"text":"And it was dropping at such a rate"},{"time":62120,"text":"that it would have left the drinking water\nintakes for Las Vegas high and dry."},{"time":66720,"text":"The city became so concerned about this"},{"time":69480,"text":"that they recently constructed\na new drinking water intake structure"},{"time":73440,"text":"that they referred to as the \"Third Straw\""},{"time":75520,"text":"to pull water out\nof the greater depths of the lake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79080,"text":"The challenges associated\nwith providing water to a modern city"},{"time":82760,"text":"are not restricted\nto the American Southwest."},{"time":85840,"text":"In the year 2007, the third largest\ncity in Australia, Brisbane,"},{"time":91200,"text":"came within 6 months\nof running out of water."},{"time":94160,"text":"A similar drama is playing out today\nin SÃ£o Paulo, Brazil,"},{"time":98440,"text":"where the main reservoir for the city"},{"time":100280,"text":"has gone from being\ncompletely full in 2010,"},{"time":103200,"text":"to being nearly empty today"},{"time":105400,"text":"as the city approaches\nthe 2016 Summer Olympics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"For those of us who are fortunate enough"},{"time":112560,"text":"to live in one\nof the world's great cities,"},{"time":114640,"text":"we've never truly experienced\nthe effects of a catastrophic drought."},{"time":118800,"text":"We like to complain\nabout the navy showers we have to take."},{"time":122560,"text":"We like our neighbors to see\nour dirty cars and our brown lawns."},{"time":126960,"text":"But we've never really faced\nthe prospect of turning on the tap"},{"time":130520,"text":"and having nothing come out."},{"time":132920,"text":"And that's because when things\nhave gotten bad in the past,"},{"time":135760,"text":"it's always been possible\nto expand a reservoir"},{"time":138840,"text":"or dig a few more groundwater wells."},{"time":142080,"text":"Well, in a time when all\nof the water resources are spoken for,"},{"time":145960,"text":"it's not going to be possible\nto rely on this tried and true way"},{"time":149360,"text":"of providing ourselves with water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151720,"text":"Some people think that we're going\nto solve the urban water problem"},{"time":155520,"text":"by taking water from our rural neighbors."},{"time":158400,"text":"But that's an approach that's fraught\nwith political, legal and social dangers."},{"time":164680,"text":"And even if we succeed in grabbing\nthe water from our rural neighbors,"},{"time":168240,"text":"we're just transferring\nthe problem to someone else"},{"time":170760,"text":"and there's a good chance\nit will come back and bite us"},{"time":173400,"text":"in the form of higher food prices"},{"time":175320,"text":"and damage to the aquatic ecosystems\nthat already rely upon that water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180200,"text":"I think that there's a better way\nto solve our urban water crisis"},{"time":183600,"text":"and I think that's to open up\nfour new local sources of water"},{"time":188040,"text":"that I liken to faucets."},{"time":189800,"text":"If we can make smart investments\nin these new sources of water"},{"time":193920,"text":"in the coming years,"},{"time":195240,"text":"we can solve our urban water problem"},{"time":197600,"text":"and decrease the likelihood\nthat we'll ever run across"},{"time":200960,"text":"the effects of a catastrophic drought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204280,"text":"Now, if you told me 20 years ago"},{"time":206360,"text":"that a modern city could exist\nwithout a supply of imported water,"},{"time":211000,"text":"I probably would have dismissed you\nas an unrealistic and uninformed dreamer."},{"time":215480,"text":"But my own experiences"},{"time":217040,"text":"working with some of the world's most\nwater-starved cities in the last decades"},{"time":221440,"text":"have shown me that we have\nthe technologies and the management skills"},{"time":225400,"text":"to actually transition away\nfrom imported water,"},{"time":228320,"text":"and that's what I want\nto tell you about tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231240,"text":"The first source of local water\nsupply that we need to develop"},{"time":235640,"text":"to solve our urban water problem"},{"time":237800,"text":"will flow with the rainwater\nthat falls in our cities."},{"time":241080,"text":"One of the great tragedies\nof urban development"},{"time":244520,"text":"is that as our cities grew,"},{"time":246520,"text":"we started covering all the surfaces\nwith concrete and asphalt."},{"time":250200,"text":"And when we did that,\nwe had to build storm sewers"},{"time":252640,"text":"to get the water\nthat fell on the cities out"},{"time":254760,"text":"before it could cause flooding,"},{"time":256720,"text":"and that's a waste\nof a vital water resource."},{"time":260200,"text":"Let me give you an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"This figure here shows you\nthe volume of water"},{"time":265240,"text":"that could be collected\nin the city of San Jose"},{"time":267880,"text":"if they could harvest the stormwater\nthat fell within the city limits."},{"time":271680,"text":"You can see from the intersection\nof the blue line and the black dotted line"},{"time":276480,"text":"that if San Jose could just capture half\nof the water that fell within the city,"},{"time":280800,"text":"they'd have enough water\nto get them through an entire year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284160,"text":"Now, I know what some of you\nare probably thinking."},{"time":286800,"text":"\"The answer to our problem\nis to start building great big tanks"},{"time":290400,"text":"and attaching them\nto the downspouts of our roof gutters,"},{"time":293280,"text":"rainwater harvesting.\""},{"time":295160,"text":"Now, that's an idea\nthat might work in some places."},{"time":297600,"text":"But if you live in a place\nwhere it mainly rains in the winter time"},{"time":300880,"text":"and most of the water demand\nis in the summertime,"},{"time":303320,"text":"it's not a very cost-effective way\nto solve a water problem."},{"time":307080,"text":"And if you experience the effects\nof a multiyear drought,"},{"time":310120,"text":"like California's currently experiencing,"},{"time":312320,"text":"you just can't build a rainwater tank\nthat's big enough to solve your problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316560,"text":"I think there's a lot more practical way"},{"time":318600,"text":"to harvest the stormwater and\nthe rainwater that falls in our cities,"},{"time":322120,"text":"and that's to capture it\nand let it percolate into the ground."},{"time":325920,"text":"After all, many of our cities are sitting\non top of a natural water storage system"},{"time":331120,"text":"that can accommodate\nhuge volumes of water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334240,"text":"For example, historically,\nLos Angeles has obtained"},{"time":337920,"text":"about a third of its water supply\nfrom a massive aquifer"},{"time":340960,"text":"that underlies the San Fernando Valley."},{"time":344400,"text":"Now, when you look at the water\nthat comes off of your roof"},{"time":347200,"text":"and runs off of your lawn\nand flows down the gutter,"},{"time":349680,"text":"you might say to yourself,\n\"Do I really want to drink that stuff?\""},{"time":353520,"text":"Well, the answer is\nyou don't want to drink it"},{"time":355720,"text":"until it's been treated a little bit."},{"time":357560,"text":"And so the challenge that we face\nin urban water harvesting"},{"time":360680,"text":"is to capture the water, clean the water"},{"time":363440,"text":"and get it underground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365520,"text":"And that's exactly\nwhat the city of Los Angeles is doing"},{"time":368560,"text":"with a new project that they're building\nin Burbank, California."},{"time":372680,"text":"This figure here shows\nthe stormwater park that they're building"},{"time":376800,"text":"by hooking a series of stormwater\ncollection systems, or storm sewers,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and routing that water\ninto an abandoned gravel quarry."},{"time":385600,"text":"The water that's captured in the quarry"},{"time":387520,"text":"is slowly passed\nthrough a man-made wetland,"},{"time":390320,"text":"and then it goes\ninto that ball field there"},{"time":392960,"text":"and percolates into the ground,"},{"time":394920,"text":"recharging the drinking water\naquifer of the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397960,"text":"And in the process\nof passing through the wetland"},{"time":401000,"text":"and percolating through the ground,"},{"time":402800,"text":"the water encounters microbes\nthat live on the surfaces of the plants"},{"time":406320,"text":"and the surfaces of the soil,"},{"time":407920,"text":"and that purifies the water."},{"time":410160,"text":"And if the water's\nstill not clean enough to drink"},{"time":412560,"text":"after it's been through\nthis natural treatment process,"},{"time":415280,"text":"the city can treat it again"},{"time":416640,"text":"when they pump if back out\nof the groundwater aquifers"},{"time":419240,"text":"before they deliver it to people to drink."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422440,"text":"The second tap that we need to open up\nto solve our urban water problem"},{"time":426840,"text":"will flow with the wastewater"},{"time":428320,"text":"that comes out\nof our sewage treatment plants."},{"time":431360,"text":"Now, many of you are probably familiar\nwith the concept of recycled water."},{"time":434861,"text":"You've probably seen signs like this"},{"time":436760,"text":"that tell you that the shrubbery\nand the highway median"},{"time":440040,"text":"and the local golf course"},{"time":441560,"text":"is being watered with water"},{"time":443440,"text":"that used to be\nin a sewage treatment plant."},{"time":446400,"text":"We've been doing this\nfor a couple of decades now."},{"time":449360,"text":"But what we're learning\nfrom our experience"},{"time":451400,"text":"is that this approach is much more\nexpensive that we expected it to be."},{"time":455520,"text":"Because once we build\nthe first few water recycling systems"},{"time":458640,"text":"close to the sewage treatment plant,"},{"time":460440,"text":"we have to build longer\nand longer pipe networks"},{"time":462703,"text":"to get that water to where it needs to go."},{"time":465600,"text":"And that becomes prohibitive\nin terms of cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"What we're finding is"},{"time":470240,"text":"that a much more cost-effective\nand practical way of recycling wastewater"},{"time":474280,"text":"is to turn treated wastewater\ninto drinking water"},{"time":476880,"text":"through a two-step process."},{"time":479080,"text":"In the first step in this process\nwe pressurize the water"},{"time":482240,"text":"and pass it through\na reverse osmosis membrane:"},{"time":485000,"text":"a thin, permeable plastic membrane"},{"time":487440,"text":"that allows water molecules\nto pass through"},{"time":490000,"text":"but traps and retains the salts,\nthe viruses and the organic chemicals"},{"time":494800,"text":"that might be present in the wastewater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497520,"text":"In the second step in the process,"},{"time":499480,"text":"we add a small amount of hydrogen peroxide"},{"time":502000,"text":"and shine ultraviolet light on the water."},{"time":504720,"text":"The ultraviolet light\ncleaves the hydrogen peroxide"},{"time":507640,"text":"into two parts that are called\nhydroxyl radicals,"},{"time":510800,"text":"and these hydroxyl radicals\nare very potent forms of oxygen"},{"time":514919,"text":"that break down most organic chemicals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518120,"text":"After the water's been\nthrough this two-stage process,"},{"time":521200,"text":"it's safe to drink."},{"time":522840,"text":"I know,"},{"time":524120,"text":"I've been studying recycled water"},{"time":526720,"text":"using every measurement technique\nknown to modern science"},{"time":530160,"text":"for the past 15 years."},{"time":532320,"text":"We've detected some chemicals"},{"time":533760,"text":"that can make it through\nthe first step in the process,"},{"time":536360,"text":"but by the time we get to the second step,"},{"time":538384,"text":"the advanced oxidation process,"},{"time":540320,"text":"we rarely see any chemicals present."},{"time":542760,"text":"And that's in stark contrast\nto the taken-for-granted water supplies"},{"time":546960,"text":"that we regularly drink all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550040,"text":"There's another way we can recycle water."},{"time":552440,"text":"This is an engineered treatment wetland\nthat we recently built"},{"time":555560,"text":"on the Santa Ana River\nin Southern California."},{"time":558360,"text":"The treatment wetland receives water\nfrom a part of the Santa Ana River"},{"time":562480,"text":"that in the summertime consists\nalmost entirely of wastewater effluent"},{"time":566120,"text":"from cities like Riverside\nand San Bernardino."},{"time":569160,"text":"The water comes\ninto our treatment wetland,"},{"time":571240,"text":"it's exposed to sunlight and algae"},{"time":573600,"text":"and those break down\nthe organic chemicals,"},{"time":576120,"text":"remove the nutrients\nand inactivate the waterborne pathogens."},{"time":579680,"text":"The water gets put back\nin the Santa Ana River,"},{"time":582160,"text":"it flows down to Anaheim,"},{"time":584080,"text":"gets taken out at Anaheim\nand percolated into the ground,"},{"time":587360,"text":"and becomes the drinking water\nof the city of Anaheim,"},{"time":590040,"text":"completing the trip\nfrom the sewers of Riverside County"},{"time":594000,"text":"to the drinking water supply\nof Orange County."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598000,"text":"Now, you might think\nthat this idea of drinking wastewater"},{"time":601440,"text":"is some sort of futuristic fantasy\nor not commonly done."},{"time":604880,"text":"Well, in California, we already recycle\nabout 40 billion gallons a year"},{"time":609280,"text":"of wastewater through the two-stage\nadvanced treatment process"},{"time":612400,"text":"I was telling you about."},{"time":613720,"text":"That's enough water to be\nthe supply of about a million people"},{"time":617480,"text":"if it were their sole water supply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620280,"text":"The third tap that we need to open up\nwill not be a tap at all,"},{"time":624520,"text":"it will be a kind of virtual tap,"},{"time":626160,"text":"it will be the water conservation\nthat we manage to do."},{"time":629280,"text":"And the place where we need to think\nabout water conservation is outdoors"},{"time":632760,"text":"because in California\nand other modern American cities,"},{"time":636400,"text":"about half of our water use\nhappens outdoors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639760,"text":"In the current drought,"},{"time":641240,"text":"we've seen that it's possible"},{"time":642840,"text":"to have our lawns survive\nand our plants survive"},{"time":645840,"text":"with about half as much water."},{"time":647760,"text":"So there's no need\nto start painting concrete green"},{"time":650800,"text":"and putting in Astroturf\nand buying cactuses."},{"time":653920,"text":"We can have California-friendly\nlandscaping with soil moisture detectors"},{"time":658160,"text":"and smart irrigation controllers"},{"time":660080,"text":"and have beautiful\ngreen landscapes in our cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663760,"text":"The fourth and final water tap\nthat we need to open up"},{"time":666800,"text":"to solve our urban water problem"},{"time":668720,"text":"will flow with desalinated seawater."},{"time":671360,"text":"Now, I know what you probably heard\npeople say about seawater desalination."},{"time":675360,"text":"\"It's a great thing to do if you have\nlots of oil, not a lot of water"},{"time":679560,"text":"and you don't care about climate change.\""},{"time":681960,"text":"Seawater desalination is energy-intensive\nno matter how you slice it."},{"time":686320,"text":"But that characterization\nof seawater desalination"},{"time":688960,"text":"as being a nonstarter\nis hopelessly out of date."},{"time":692000,"text":"We've made tremendous progress\nin seawater desalination"},{"time":694800,"text":"in the past two decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696920,"text":"This picture shows you"},{"time":698600,"text":"the largest seawater desalination plant\nin the Western hemisphere"},{"time":702600,"text":"that's currently being built\nnorth of San Diego."},{"time":705440,"text":"Compared to the seawater\ndesalination plant"},{"time":707720,"text":"that was built in\nSanta Barbara 25 years ago,"},{"time":711040,"text":"this treatment plant\nwill use about half the energy"},{"time":713720,"text":"to produce a gallon of water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715840,"text":"But just because seawater desalination\nhas become less energy-intensive,"},{"time":719600,"text":"doesn't mean we should start building\ndesalination plants everywhere."},{"time":722863,"text":"Among the different choices we have,"},{"time":724623,"text":"it's probably the most energy-intensive"},{"time":726760,"text":"and potentially environmentally damaging"},{"time":728720,"text":"of the options to create\na local water supply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732560,"text":"So there it is."},{"time":733800,"text":"With these four sources of water,"},{"time":735600,"text":"we can move away\nfrom our reliance on imported water."},{"time":739680,"text":"Through reform in the way we landscape\nour surfaces and our properties,"},{"time":744200,"text":"we can reduce outdoor water use\nby about 50 percent,"},{"time":747320,"text":"thereby increasing \nthe water supply by 25 percent."},{"time":750800,"text":"We can recycle the water\nthat makes it into the sewer,"},{"time":753348,"text":"thereby increasing\nour water supply by 40 percent."},{"time":756880,"text":"And we can make up the difference\nthrough a combination"},{"time":759520,"text":"of stormwater harvesting\nand seawater desalination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763280,"text":"So, let's create a water supply"},{"time":767120,"text":"that will be able\nto withstand any of the challenges"},{"time":770800,"text":"that climate change throws at us\nin the coming years."},{"time":773400,"text":"Let's create a water supply\nthat uses local sources"},{"time":776760,"text":"and leaves more water\nin the environment for fish and for food."},{"time":781640,"text":"Let's create a water system that's\nconsistent with out environmental values."},{"time":786680,"text":"And let's do it for our children\nand our grandchildren"},{"time":790160,"text":"and let's tell them this is the system"},{"time":792800,"text":"that they have to\ntake care of in the future"},{"time":795160,"text":"because it's our last chance\nto create a new kind of water system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799120,"text":"Thank you very much for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801002,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}